The NCBO Ontology Recommender invoked the NCBO Annotator [26] to identify all annotations for the input data. The NCBO Annotator is a BioPortal service that annotates textual data with ontology classes. Then, the Ontology Recommender scored all BioPortal ontologies as a function of the number and relevance of the annotations found, and ranked the ontologies according to those scores. The first ontology in the ranking would be suggested as the most appropriate for the input data. The score for each ontology was calculated according to the following formula4:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
