It is crucial that ontology recommendation systems suggest ontologies that provide high coverage of the input data. As with the original approach, the new recommendation process is driven by the annotations provided by the NCBO Annotator, but the method used to evaluate the candidate ontologies is different. In the new algorithm, each annotation is assigned a score computed in accordance with the following expression5:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
